\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999975739713005, \"rank\": 2.4259778811534767e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2643, \"end\": 2646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.193435227230732e-27, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Silver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Silver\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Silver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Silver\"}, {\"begin\": 2676, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2693, \"end\": 2708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organizers are working to meet that promise.\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  \\\"They understand we independently need to be satisfied,\\\" Silver said in an interview in Paris, whereThe Athleticspent more than a week last month reporting this story.\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2942, \"end\": 2947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When local organizers first envisioned the 2024 Games nearly 10 years ago, they had the full, two-week basketball events planned for Accor Arena, a 16,000-seat venue in Paris that is very similar to many NBA venues.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3156, \"end\": 3167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Accor Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}, {\"begin\": 3192, \"end\": 3197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3227, \"end\": 3230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.193435227230732e-27, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheCleveland CavaliersandBrooklyn Netsplayed there Jan. 11.\", \"from\": 3239, \"to\": 3298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That changed in early 2022, with soaring Olympic costs brought on in part by the pandemic that prompted Paris organizers to nix construction of a new swimming venue.\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3404, \"end\": 3409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of that, officials had to rethink numerous events, and moved swimming to an arena originally expected to be used for gymnastics.\", \"from\": 3466, \"to\": 3602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, Accor Arena will host gymnastics while the basketball tournaments' group stages unfold in Lille, and then basketball will move to Accor for the medal rounds after gymnastics concludes.\", \"from\": 3603, \"to\": 3792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3608, \"end\": 3619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Accor Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}, {\"begin\": 3698, \"end\": 3703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 3738, \"end\": 3743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Accor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My job is to balance the different sports,\\\" Tony Estanguet, a three-time French gold medalist in canoeing who is president of the Paris 2024 organizing committee, said in an interview at his Saint-Denis office.\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 4005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3839, \"end\": 3853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 3868, \"end\": 3874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999865095633613, \"rank\": 1.3472770318316186e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3925, \"end\": 3935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.693249840208634e-52, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The power of the Games is to make sure that there is a good place for (track and field), for swimming, for gymnastics, for basketball, for volleyball, for handball, for judo, for 54 sports.\\\"\", \"from\": 4006, \"to\": 4197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee groups sports by popularity, and the most important get the most money and preference, according to the Association of Summer Olympic International Federations.\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4203, \"end\": 4234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnastics is one of three sports in the top group, with swimming and track and field, while basketball is in the second grouping.\", \"from\": 4396, \"to\": 4526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4396, \"end\": 4406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.999999995705366, \"rank\": 4.2949770006457475e-09, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Multiple presidents of basketball federations around the world say the IOC's tiered system is why gymnastics has often been staged in arenas that are normally used for hoops outside the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4598, \"end\": 4601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.730459367470642e-49, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But badminton, instead of basketball, at the other basketball arena in town - that is different.\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the north end of Paris, near a station for express trains to Lille, is the sparkling new, $200 million Adidas Arena with NBA-caliber amenities.\", \"from\": 4822, \"to\": 4968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4842, \"end\": 4847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4886, \"end\": 4891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 4928, \"end\": 4934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was built with the help of Olympic funds as a basketball arena and its main tenant is Paris Basketball, a pro team that competes in the French Ligue Nationale de Basket and the EuroCup.\", \"from\": 4969, \"to\": 5157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5108, \"end\": 5114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999865095633613, \"rank\": 1.3472770318316186e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That team opened Adidas Arena with a game there on Sunday, and the gym was called \\\"a pure gem, right down to its finishes\\\" by the notable French basketball journalist Arnaud Lecomte.\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5175, \"end\": 5181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}, {\"begin\": 5296, \"end\": 5302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999865095633613, \"rank\": 1.3472770318316186e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  \\\"This arena was requested by us,\\\" said Andreas Zagklis, secretary general of FIBA, the international governing body for basketball.\", \"from\": 5342, \"to\": 5488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5396, \"end\": 5411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andreas_Zagklis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andreas Zagklis\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andreas_Zagklis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andreas_Zagklis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was not offered to us, and I would leave it at that.\\\"\", \"from\": 5489, \"to\": 5546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris organizers still wanted to keep basketball in Paris, and considered an auxiliary conference hall on the southwest side of the city as an alternative.\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5548, \"end\": 5553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5600, \"end\": 5605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Exhibition Hall 6 at Porte de Versailles, Paris' main convention center, has low-hanging rafters and open air ducts.\", \"from\": 5705, \"to\": 5821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5726, \"end\": 5745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Porte_de_Versailles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999417923, \"rank\": 5.7785942206079065e-11, \"text\": \"Porte de Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Porte_de_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Porte_de_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 5747, \"end\": 5752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Huge steel beams in the middle of the concrete floor stretch to the ceiling.\", \"from\": 5822, \"to\": 5898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a perfect venue for a giant trade show.\", \"from\": 5899, \"to\": 5943, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But not for an elite basketball tournament.\", \"from\": 5944, \"to\": 5987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was nonsense,\\\" said Jean-Pierre Siutat, president of the French basketball federation.\", \"from\": 5989, \"to\": 6079, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6013, \"end\": 6024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dardenne_brothers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6290420587173306e-27, \"text\": \"Jean-Pierre\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dardenne_brothers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dardenne_brothers\"}, {\"begin\": 6050, \"end\": 6078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Federation_of_Basketball\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French basketball federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Federation_of_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Federation_of_Basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"People begin to react.\", \"from\": 6080, \"to\": 6103, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"FIBA said no, come on.\", \"from\": 6104, \"to\": 6126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6104, \"end\": 6108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"score\": 0.9999996728147915, \"rank\": 3.271856823831712e-07, \"text\": \"FIBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We want to be in Paris.\", \"from\": 6127, \"to\": 6150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6144, \"end\": 6149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But you have to find another place than this one.\", \"from\": 6151, \"to\": 6200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So for us, the best would be in (Adidas Arena).\\\"\", \"from\": 6201, \"to\": 6249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6234, \"end\": 6240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adidas Arena had been earmarked for badminton, a sport that is extremely popular in several Asian countries, with nations like China, Indonesia and South Korea having strong showings at previous Olympics.\", \"from\": 6251, \"to\": 6455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6251, \"end\": 6257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}, {\"begin\": 6343, \"end\": 6348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 0.9998870840535531, \"rank\": 8.421010948507485e-05, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 6378, \"end\": 6383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999998793291598, \"rank\": 1.1965720746742024e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 6385, \"end\": 6394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9999845632519322, \"rank\": 1.3417902660965866e-05, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}, {\"begin\": 6399, \"end\": 6410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1542667693833888e-13, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plans for the sport had not been touched amid the shuffling of other major competitions.\", \"from\": 6456, \"to\": 6544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With basketball in flux, its stakeholders turned their attention toward the Paris 2024 organizing committee and \\u00c9tienne Thobois - its second in charge under Estanguet.\", \"from\": 6546, \"to\": 6713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6622, \"end\": 6632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.693249840208634e-52, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thobois is a former Olympic badminton player who is on the executive committee for the World Badminton Federation.\", \"from\": 6714, \"to\": 6828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6801, \"end\": 6827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Badminton_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Badminton Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Badminton_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Badminton_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zagklis lobbied Thobois, then Estanguet directly to move badminton to accommodate basketball.\", \"from\": 6830, \"to\": 6923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials for the city of Paris said they similarly pushed without success.\", \"from\": 6924, \"to\": 6999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6950, \"end\": 6955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet disputed the characterizations by FIBA and city officials of the negotiations, and Paris 2024 denied a request byThe Athleticto speak directly with Thobois.\", \"from\": 7001, \"to\": 7167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7094, \"end\": 7104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.693249840208634e-52, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet called it \\\"ridiculous\\\" to suggest that it was Thobois' decision to keep badminton at Adidas Arena.\", \"from\": 7168, \"to\": 7276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7263, \"end\": 7269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  \\\"He was not involved in particular on this topic,\\\" Estanguet said.\", \"from\": 7278, \"to\": 7359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had the discussions with FIBA, I had the discussion with the IOC.\\\"\", \"from\": 7360, \"to\": 7429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7424, \"end\": 7427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.730459367470642e-49, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris city officials said the reason given to deny their request wasn't a simple diplomatic rejection.\", \"from\": 7431, \"to\": 7533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7431, \"end\": 7436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thobois, they said, cited a height requirement for a badminton ceiling - a minimum of 39.3 feet, which Adidas Arena met.\", \"from\": 7534, \"to\": 7654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7637, \"end\": 7643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(International basketball rules call for ceilings of at least 29.5 feet.\", \"from\": 7655, \"to\": 7727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Exhibition Hall 6 meets the threshold but would have trouble with a high-arcing, midcourt heave from a player likeStephen Curry.)\", \"from\": 7728, \"to\": 7857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We studied it after (Thobois) said no, because he had a lot of pressure, especially because he played badminton,\\\" said Pierre Rabadan, the deputy mayor for sport in Paris, adding that badminton's only other viable option was \\\"going somewhere like two or three hours from Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 7859, \"to\": 8138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7979, \"end\": 7993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre Rabadan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\"}, {\"begin\": 8025, \"end\": 8030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 8131, \"end\": 8136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rabadan said city and Olympic officials determined that the costs to move badminton outside of Paris were not feasible.\", \"from\": 8140, \"to\": 8259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8140, \"end\": 8147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rabadan\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rabadan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rabadan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rabadan\"}, {\"begin\": 8235, \"end\": 8240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Building a temporary venue in Paris, like organizers are doing outdoors for three-on-three basketball, was also out of the question because ofbadminton's need for wind control.\", \"from\": 8260, \"to\": 8436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8290, \"end\": 8295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The leaders of badminton appreciated the lack of disruption for its events.\", \"from\": 8438, \"to\": 8513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are very happy with the badminton competition being played at the world-class (Adidas Arena) based on the specific technical requirements of our sport, and this has been the plan from Day 1,\\\" Thomas Lund, secretary general for the World Badminton Federation, said in an email.\", \"from\": 8515, \"to\": 8795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8598, \"end\": 8604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}, {\"begin\": 8711, \"end\": 8722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Lund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.899504739876642e-19, \"text\": \"Thomas Lund\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Lund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Lund\"}, {\"begin\": 8750, \"end\": 8776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Badminton_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Badminton Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Badminton_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Badminton_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have not had any conversations with Paris 2024 or the IOC to suggest anything other than this original plan.\\\"\", \"from\": 8796, \"to\": 8909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8836, \"end\": 8846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.693249840208634e-52, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 8854, \"end\": 8857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.730459367470642e-49, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Basketball, with the star power in both the men's and women's divisions, is expected to remain a huge ticket seller in Lille.\", \"from\": 8911, \"to\": 9036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9030, \"end\": 9035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The decisions are not sitting well with some people in the basketball world, who see Thobois' ties to badminton as a conflict of interest in the decision-making.\", \"from\": 9038, \"to\": 9199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  \\\"The idea that you can not do a pop-up badminton stadium \\u2026 it's absurdist,\\\" said David Kahn, the president and co-founder of Paris Basketball, and one of the lead consultants on the development of Adidas Arena.\", \"from\": 9201, \"to\": 9426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9297, \"end\": 9307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Kahn_(writer)\", \"score\": 0.9704648518036444, \"rank\": 0.030430430430445226, \"text\": \"David Kahn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Kahn_(writer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Kahn_(writer)\"}, {\"begin\": 9341, \"end\": 9357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Basketball\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 9413, \"end\": 9419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kahn was also the point person for theIndiana Pacersin the design of Gainbridge Fieldhouse, which will hostthe NBA All-Star Gameon Sunday.\", \"from\": 9427, \"to\": 9565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9496, \"end\": 9517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainbridge_Fieldhouse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gainbridge Fieldhouse\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainbridge_Fieldhouse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainbridge_Fieldhouse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's especially absurd when you compare it to the impact of basketball here culturally,\\\" Kahn added.\", \"from\": 9567, \"to\": 9668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He echoed the sentiments of several basketball officialsThe Athleticspoke with when he said: \\\"Everybody in Paris knows the No.\", \"from\": 9669, \"to\": 9795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9776, \"end\": 9781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2 person in Paris 2024 is a former badminton player and high-ranking badminton official.\", \"from\": 9796, \"to\": 9884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9808, \"end\": 9818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.693249840208634e-52, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How he could co-opt the only new indoor arena being built for these Olympics - and for the city's basketball legacy - is a question that needs to be answered.\\\"\", \"from\": 9885, \"to\": 10044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet said the higher capacity at the Lille soccer stadium - 27,000 seats vs. 8,000 at Adidas Arena - is a good thing for the basketball tournaments.\", \"from\": 10046, \"to\": 10199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10088, \"end\": 10093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are still likely to attract big crowds, he said, while badminton can draw fans, too, by competing in the heart of Paris.\", \"from\": 10200, \"to\": 10325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10319, \"end\": 10324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Basketball is now in the position of the top sports,\\\" Estanguet said.\", \"from\": 10327, \"to\": 10397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If I could have this idea at the beginning, I would have loved it.\", \"from\": 10398, \"to\": 10465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not have it, but I strongly believe that this is the best we could have.\\\"\", \"from\": 10466, \"to\": 10545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lille has much of its own charm, and USA Basketball is taking measures to help its players and their families see plenty of Paris during the Games.\", \"from\": 10547, \"to\": 10694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10547, \"end\": 10552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 10584, \"end\": 10598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999701506192962, \"rank\": 2.9850271283272776e-05, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 10671, \"end\": 10676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organizers are building a satellite village for athletes in Lille, but the American men and women - along with the French men - will not stay there.\", \"from\": 10695, \"to\": 10851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10763, \"end\": 10768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 10778, \"end\": 10786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.572891672654191e-16, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 10818, \"end\": 10824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999865095633613, \"rank\": 1.3472770318316186e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French men's team has its own hotel.\", \"from\": 10852, \"to\": 10892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10856, \"end\": 10862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999865095633613, \"rank\": 1.3472770318316186e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USA Basketball, whose officials declined to comment for this story, has made concurrent arrangements in Paris and Lille for the men's and women's teams, and will figure out how to use both.\", \"from\": 10893, \"to\": 11082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10893, \"end\": 10907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999701506192962, \"rank\": 2.9850271283272776e-05, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 10997, \"end\": 11002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 11007, \"end\": 11012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did hear about (Lille) and I was like, 'Ooooh, that's gonna be a drive, or however we are gonna get there,'\\\" said USA women's starA'ja Wilson.\", \"from\": 11084, \"to\": 11229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11201, \"end\": 11204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.2321431855830613e-12, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 11222, \"end\": 11228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"score\": 0.9999999977617335, \"rank\": 2.2381595943531597e-09, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But, no, I am excited.\", \"from\": 11230, \"to\": 11253, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At that point, we are at the Olympics, so I am good for everything.\\\"\", \"from\": 11254, \"to\": 11322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond transportation, another practical concern looms.\", \"from\": 11324, \"to\": 11379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  Just outside of Lille, the Pierre-Mauroy soccer stadium being converted to host basketball, is a 50,000-seat venue with a retractable roof.\", \"from\": 11381, \"to\": 11535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11412, \"end\": 11417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organizers gaveThe Athletica tour of the stadium last month.\", \"from\": 11536, \"to\": 11604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The north half of the field lifts off the ground and folds on top of the southern half, creating a hole 23 feet deep, with plenty of room for a basketball court.\", \"from\": 11605, \"to\": 11766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stadium workers will run a massive curtain across the middle of the stadium, separating temporary practice courts from the rest of the venue.\", \"from\": 11767, \"to\": 11908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The EuroBasket - a tournament for European men's national teams - was held there in September of 2015 and was regarded as a success.\", \"from\": 11909, \"to\": 12041, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the EuroBasket in Lille was a fall event, when crisper air led to more comfortable court conditions.\", \"from\": 12043, \"to\": 12147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12065, \"end\": 12070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The stadium does not have air conditioning - a problem for FIBA and the NBA for Olympic games in the middle of the summer.\", \"from\": 12148, \"to\": 12270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12220, \"end\": 12223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.193435227230732e-27, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lambis Konstantinidis, director of planning and coordination for Paris 2024, said the solution is a temporary, \\\"typical sort of cooling system.\\\"\", \"from\": 12272, \"to\": 12416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12337, \"end\": 12347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.693249840208634e-52, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is a catch.\", \"from\": 12417, \"to\": 12438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because soccer is in season, the system will not be installed until mid-June at the earliest.\", \"from\": 12439, \"to\": 12532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That has drawn the personal attention of Silver, with basketball executives fretting about the possibility of cramping and other injuries if star players compete in less-than-ideal conditions.\", \"from\": 12534, \"to\": 12726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have all engaged with independent engineers who are going to certify for us that there are appropriate circumstances in the arena,\\\" Silver said.\", \"from\": 12728, \"to\": 12876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In January 2023, while in Paris as part of the NBA's Global Games series, Silver was so concerned about the Olympic tournaments being moved to Lille that he raised the issue directly in a face-to-face meeting with Macron at the Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es presidential palace.\", \"from\": 12878, \"to\": 13141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12904, \"end\": 12909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 12925, \"end\": 12928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.193435227230732e-27, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 13021, \"end\": 13026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 13092, \"end\": 13098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.011596130215261e-30, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Macron, Silver said, gave assurances about the air conditioning and other items like support for travel to and from the heart of the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 13143, \"to\": 13288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13143, \"end\": 13149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.011596130215261e-30, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An aide to Macron confirmed Silver's account of the meeting toThe Athletic.\", \"from\": 13289, \"to\": 13364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13300, \"end\": 13306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.011596130215261e-30, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  The challenges at play will likely keep some athletes from experiencing the audacious opening ceremony, a 3.7-mile ride along the Seine, winding near many of the city's most famous landmarks.\", \"from\": 13366, \"to\": 13572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13511, \"end\": 13516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6223902213539658e-28, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Full schedules have not been released, but there are men's games the next day, July 27.\", \"from\": 13573, \"to\": 13660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"(USA) or us will play the day after,\\\" said Siutat, who heads French basketball.\", \"from\": 13662, \"to\": 13742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13724, \"end\": 13730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999865095633613, \"rank\": 1.3472770318316186e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's difficult to be in Lille, to come back, go on the boat.\", \"from\": 13743, \"to\": 13804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13768, \"end\": 13773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 Then after you take the bus and go back to (Lille).\", \"from\": 13805, \"to\": 13858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13851, \"end\": 13856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So we are not going to be (on the boats).\", \"from\": 13859, \"to\": 13900, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's a problem for the players because we know that some players want to go to the opening ceremony, especially in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 13901, \"to\": 14029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14022, \"end\": 14027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"J\\u00e9r\\u00f4me Rosenstiehl, director of basketball for the Paris games, said organizers are crafting plans to get the basketball players back to Lille late Friday if they want to attend the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 14031, \"to\": 14230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14082, \"end\": 14087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 14168, \"end\": 14173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he said \\\"it's not an issue\\\" for Olympic organizers.\", \"from\": 14231, \"to\": 14286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you look back in history, some teams that are playing on Day 1, the day after the ceremony, so they do not go.\", \"from\": 14288, \"to\": 14402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a fact,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 14403, \"to\": 14428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zagklis, the secretary general for FIBA, said his planners are working with Olympic officials so that basketball teams that do not advance past Lille can still spend a few days at the athletes' village in Paris, so they do not miss out on the experience.\", \"from\": 14430, \"to\": 14684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14465, \"end\": 14469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"score\": 0.9999996728147915, \"rank\": 3.271856823831712e-07, \"text\": \"FIBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\"}, {\"begin\": 14574, \"end\": 14579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 14635, \"end\": 14640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said he feels better about the tournaments than he did a year ago, and certainly better than he did when organizers considered moving basketball to the exhibition hall.\", \"from\": 14685, \"to\": 14856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver, while acknowledging the challenges to host the Games, conceded that basketball would be without its top pick.\", \"from\": 14858, \"to\": 14975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If we had been given a choice between being in Paris the entire time or playing the group stage in Lille, I know we would have chosen Paris,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 14977, \"to\": 15128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15025, \"end\": 15030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 15077, \"end\": 15082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 15112, \"end\": 15117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On a frigid Paris night in January, a trendy rooftop bar with a view of the Eiffel Tower, snappily dressed clientele and a DJ spinning electronic music served as a reminder of the allure of Paris.\", \"from\": 15130, \"to\": 15326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15142, \"end\": 15147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 15320, \"end\": 15325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  Boris Diaw, a past NBA champion who is now general manager for the French men's team, met withThe Athleticthere to discuss several topics, including Les Bleus' prospects of upsetting the Americans and the Olympic competition moving to Lille.\", \"from\": 15328, \"to\": 15584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15349, \"end\": 15353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0886317673467603e-23, \"text\": \"Diaw\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\"}, {\"begin\": 15362, \"end\": 15374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.565191273835245e-19, \"text\": \"NBA champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\"}, {\"begin\": 15410, \"end\": 15416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999865095633613, \"rank\": 1.3472770318316186e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 15578, \"end\": 15583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Diaw, 41, who played for Team France, scanned the bar scene and shook his head over what he and many others characterize as a missed cultural opportunity by not keeping both weeks of the tournament in Paris.\", \"from\": 15586, \"to\": 15793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15586, \"end\": 15590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0886317673467603e-23, \"text\": \"Diaw\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\"}, {\"begin\": 15611, \"end\": 15622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9810814040453176, \"rank\": 0.019282869294770494, \"text\": \"Team France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 15787, \"end\": 15792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Playing in (the exhibition hall) would have been a mistake,\\\" Diaw said.\", \"from\": 15795, \"to\": 15867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15857, \"end\": 15861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0886317673467603e-23, \"text\": \"Diaw\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Diaw\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Playing in Lille, itself, is not a mistake.\", \"from\": 15868, \"to\": 15912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15880, \"end\": 15885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999985116439509, \"rank\": 1.4883578669540848e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What is not ideal is not playing in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 15913, \"to\": 15956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15949, \"end\": 15954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Top illustration of Adidas Arena, Paris' new basketball arena that will host badminton at the Olympics: Daniel Goldfarb /The Athletic; photo: Foc Kan / Getty Images)  Spot the pattern.\", \"from\": 15958, \"to\": 16143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15979, \"end\": 15985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.338637632935554e-47, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}, {\"begin\": 15993, \"end\": 15998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.051324341783033e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 16101, \"end\": 16104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fusarium_oxysporum_f.sp._cubense\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5387058263126605e-15, \"text\": \"Foc\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fusarium_oxysporum_f.sp._cubense\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fusarium_oxysporum_f.sp._cubense\"}, {\"begin\": 16111, \"end\": 16116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._Paul_Getty_Museum\", \"score\": 0.83679716976